					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
						<summary>Fourth Book of Arba'ah Ṭurim, Ṭur ḥoshen mishpaṭ, of Jacob ben Asher.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
							<locus from="1r" to="320v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Ṭur ḥoshen mishpaṭ</title>
							<title n="0" xml:lang="he">טור חשן משפט</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/314808179">Jacob ben Asher</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/314808179">יעקב בן אשר</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Folios 1r-11v contain the preface and the index. The latter breaks off abruptly with the paragraph 330. The last paragraph in the text bears the number 429.</p>
								<p>Certain parts of the colophon are damaged and hardly legible, among them the dating. Margoliouth read it as 'shnat 20', that is, [51]20 (1360).</p>
							</note>
							<decoNote type="miniature">1 miniature and full foliate border. <locus n="14r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="initial">Numerous decorated initial words with red and blue pen-flourishing. </decoNote>
							<decoNote type="border">Numerous pen-flourishing around initial words spreading into the margins creating a partial border in colours and gold.<locus from="242r" to="320v"/>
							</decoNote>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">אני<name type="person" role="scribe"> יהודה ב"ר יוסף</name> [דביי]נא זצ"ל סיימתי זה הספר טור חשן המשפט יום א' פרשה ונתתי שלו[ם בא]רץ כי"ר כ"ח לספיר' העומר שנת <date calendar="Hebrew">ע[שרי]ם לפרט קטן</date>. ברוך הנותן ליעף כח ולאין אונים עצמה ירבה. כתבתיהו לר' <name type="person" role="patron">גרשם בכ"ר יקותיאל</name> יצ"ו להגות בו הוא וזרעו וזרע זרעו אחריו עד סוף כל הדורו.<locus n="320v"/>
							</colophon>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>320 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>190</height>
										<width>145</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>120/115</height>
										<width>90/85</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>320 folios (+ 3 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>41 quires: i10 (folios 1-10), ii3 (folios 11-13), iii-vi8 (folios 14-45), vii6 (folios 46-51), viii-xxvii8 (folios 52-211), xxviii6 (folios 212-217), xxix-xli8 (folios 218-320a), marked with vertical catchwords at the end.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Slightly water-damaged (upper margins).</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="33" writtenLines="32">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Visible pricking and ruling in ink, page by page. </p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side of the folios indistinguishable.</p>
									<p>Last line written within the ruling.</p>
									<p>Some marginal notes in semi-cursive script. </p>
									<p>Gilt edges.</p>
									<p>Folios 12, 13 and [320a] are blank. </p>
									<p>Catchwords; one of them (on folio 182v) does not fit the present collation, since this folio is presently the third leaf of quire xxiv8.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Ashkenazi semi-cursive script of the 14th century, unpunctuated. <name type="person" role="scribe">Yehudah bar Yosef Erama</name> (?): inscribed with his name in the colophon, <date calendar="Hebrew">5120 </date>[<date calendar="Gregorian">1360</date>] (folio 320v); the name Yehudah is marked many times (e.g., folios 48v, 58v, 76v, 113v, 117r, 117v, 162v, 246v, 260r, 297r); acrostic of Yehudah (folio 320v).</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Rabbi <name type="person" role="patron">Gershom ben Yeḳutiel</name>: inscribed with his name in the colophon, 5120 [1360] (folio 320v).</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM in-house.</p>
								<p>Spine title: 'Jacob ben Asher. Tur Choshen Ham-Mishpat. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 27,137.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
